315 269 1000 (Multi-thread Considerations) 1000 SB
32 0 0 42 42 0 0 0 38 /Times-Roman /font32 ANSIFont font
315 384 1789 (The compiler requires a command-line switch to indicate that
code is being compiled for a multi-threaded) 1789 SB
315 434 1710 (situation.  This is because the run-time data structure must
be protected against an interleaved update) 1710 SB
315 484 1760 (from more than one thread of execution.  Consequently,
semaphores must be used to protect the pushing) 1760 SB
315 534 1705 (and popping of  static-destruction stack for an image.
 Similarly, the initialization of a static within a) 1705 SB
315 584 459 (function must be protected.) 459 SB
315 667 1795 (A single thread is used to execute the construction of global
statics and the destruction of statics. Since the) 1795 SB
315 717 1670 (construction or destruction of items could cause new execution
threads to be created, the protection) 1670 SB
315 767 971 (mechanism is not relaxed when these functions are active) 971
SB
315 850 1743 (The compiler does not provide any automatic protection against
interleaved update of user-defined data) 1743 SB
315 900 1698 (items.  It is the programmer\222s responsibility to ensure
that such protection is in place when required.) 1698 SB
